snippet: A weeklong walkout delayed the start of the 2015-16 school year for 53,000 students and thousands of educators.
abstract: Seattle public school teachers end weeklong strike, saying they agree to new contract; classes are scheduled to resume.
lead_paragraph: A weeklong walkout delayed the start of the 2015-16 school year for 53,000 students and thousands of educators.

headline.main: Striking Seattle Teachers Poised to Return to Classroom
headline.print_headline: Seattle Teachers Poised for Return to Classes
